=head1 DESCRIPTION

Contains information about the indicators that include a set of signals
observed in an attack sequence.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Key => Str

Specific indicator keys observed in the attack sequence. For
description of the valid values for key, see Attack sequence finding
details
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/guardduty/latest/ug/guardduty_findings-summary.html#guardduty-extended-threat-detection-attack-sequence-finding-details)
in the I<Amazon GuardDuty User Guide>.


=head2 Title => Str

Title describing the indicator.


=head2 Values => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

Values associated with each indicator key. For example, if the
indicator key is C<SUSPICIOUS_NETWORK>, then the value will be the name
of the network. If the indicator key is C<ATTACK_TACTIC>, then the
value will be one of the MITRE tactics.



